    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "The simplest way to sync with mainnet is to start geth without additional argument. By default geth will sync with mainnet. You can verify that you are on the mainnet by comparing blocks from your own chain with blocks from etherscan as karalabe suggested. Sync progress can be seen with mist (and probably other DApp's like wallets) or from the geth console with `eth.syncing`.\r\n\r\nAn ethereum wallet will retrieve account balances from an Ethereum node. If that node uses its own chain with balances on your accounts it will show them to you.",
